Digital Blood Pressure Tracker – Deployment Script/Guide
Step 1 – Install XAMPP (Local Deployment)

Visual: Show XAMPP download page
Script:

Go to https://www.apachefriends.org/index.html

Download the latest version for your OS.

Run the installer and finish installation.

Open XAMPP Control Panel and start Apache and MySQL.

Verify by visiting: http://localhost
 – You should see the XAMPP welcome page.

Step 2 – Set Up Database

Visual: Open phpMyAdmin in browser
Script:

Go to http://localhost/phpmyadmin

Click New, enter database name: BloodPressureDB

Click Import, select BloodPressureDB.sql from the project folder

Click Go and verify tables users and bp_readings are created

Step 3 – Copy Project Files

Visual: Show project folder in file explorer
Script:

Navigate to C:\xampp\htdocs\

Create a folder: BloodPressureTracker

Copy all HTML, CSS, JS, PHP files into this folder

Step 4 – Configure PHP Database Connection

Visual: Open register.php in VS Code
Script:

Edit PHP files (register.php, login.php, save_reading.php)

Ensure connection is:

$conn = new mysqli("localhost", "root", "", "BloodPressureDB");


Note: For XAMPP, username=root, password=leave blank

Step 5 – Run the Project Locally

Visual: Open browser, type URL
Script:

Go to: http://localhost/BloodPressureTracker/register.html

Register a new user

Login to login.html

Enter blood pressure readings and verify chart updates

Logout and test session handling

Step 6 – Deploy on Live Server (cPanel Hosting)

Visual: Show cPanel dashboard
Script:

Use FTP (FileZilla) or File Manager to upload the BloodPressureTracker folder to public_html

Go to cPanel → MySQL Databases

Create a database, a user, assign privileges

Open phpMyAdmin, select database, import BloodPressureDB.sql

Edit PHP files to update connection:

$conn = new mysqli("localhost", "your_db_user", "your_db_password", "your_db_name");


Access the app via your domain:

https://yourdomain.com/BloodPressureTracker/register.html

Step 7 – Enable HTTPS

Visual: cPanel SSL panel
Script:

Go to cPanel → SSL/TLS → Let’s Encrypt

Enable SSL for your domain/subdomain

Access the site via https:// to secure sensitive health data

Step 8 – Testing

Visual: Browser showing tracker, charts, logout/login
Script:

Register multiple users, test login/logout

Add readings to verify charts per user

Test blood pressure classification (Normal / Elevated / High)

Check database for proper records

✅ Best Practices

Use strong passwords for MySQL and users

Backup the database regularly

Sanitize inputs on PHP side to prevent SQL injection

Consider adding email verification for users
